  "prob_desc_output_spec": "Print three lines, in each line print three integers — the Little Elephant's magic square. If there are multiple magic squares, you are allowed to print any of them. Note that all numbers you print must be positive and not exceed 105. It is guaranteed that there exists at least one magic square that meets the conditions.",
  "source_code": "#include<stdio.h>\nint main()\n{\n    int x,y,z,i,j;\n    int a[3][3];\n    for(i=0;i<=2;i++)\n    for(j=0;j<=2;j++)\n    scanf(\"%d\",&a[i][j]);\n    y=(a[2][0]+a[2][1]+a[0][1]+a[0][2]-a[1][0]-a[1][2])/2;\n    x=a[2][0]+a[2][1]-y;\n    z=a[1][0]+a[1][2]-x;\n    a[0][0]=x;\n    a[1][1]=y;\n    a[2][2]=z;\n    for(i=0;i<=2;i++)\n    {\n        for(j=0;j<=2;j++)\n        printf(\"%d \",a[i][j]);\n         printf(\"\\n\");\n    }\n   return 0;\n}",
